      • create

        public static TestExecutor create(boolean validateResults,
                                  java.util.Optional<java.lang.String> extensionDir)
        Create instance.

        If validateResults is true the test will fail if the results are as expected. This is the norm. If false the test will not fail if the results differ. This is useful when re-writing the historical plans.

        Parameters:
        validateResults - flag to indicate if results should be validated.
        extensionDir - Optional extension directory.
        Returns:
        the executor.
